# Require review for infrastructure and security-sensitive files.
# Per GitHub Well-Architected SE:07 and kusari.dev security review guidance,
# CODEOWNERS should cover all files where unreviewed changes could introduce
# security vulnerabilities, leak secrets, or misdirect incident responders.

# Infrastructure as Code
terraform/       @hakunishikawa
k8s/             @hakunishikawa

# CI/CD and GitHub config
.github/         @hakunishikawa

# Container build — changes affect image security posture
Dockerfile       @hakunishikawa
.dockerignore    @hakunishikawa

# Build/deploy commands — malicious changes could exfiltrate secrets
Makefile         @hakunishikawa
docker-compose.observability.yml @hakunishikawa

# Security-sensitive documentation — changes could hide vulnerabilities,
# introduce backdoor deployment steps, or misdirect incident responders
ARCHITECTURE.md  @hakunishikawa
SECURITY.md      @hakunishikawa
DEPLOYMENT.md    @hakunishikawa
RUNBOOK.md       @hakunishikawa

# Git/editor config — removing .gitignore patterns could commit secrets
.gitignore       @hakunishikawa
